Global Phenolic Resin for Tire Rubber Market Insights
Phenolic Resin for Tire Rubber Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Phenolic Resin for Tire Rubber Market Overview
The global Phenolic Resin for Tire Rubber market is experiencing notable growth, driven by the increasing demand for high-performance tires and advancements in rubber processing technologies. The market size was valued at approximately USD 1.8 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 2.5 billion by 2030, expanding at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2025 to 2030. Phenolic resins are widely used in tire production due to their ability to enhance the heat resistance, durability, and overall performance of tires. This has spurred adoption across both the OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) and replacement tire markets. However, challenges such as the volatility in raw material prices and environmental concerns may affect market dynamics moving forward.

